==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*hagola-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[heil]], Old Saxon [[hagal]] (Dutch [[hagel]]), Old High German [[hagal]] (German [[Hagel]]), Old Norse [[hagl]] (Swedish [[hagel]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'hæjl̩/

===Noun===
'''hæġl''' ''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Old English strong declension|strong]] m'' (''pl'' '''hæġlas''')
# [[hail]]; a [[hailstorm]]
# the runic character ᚻ (/h/)

